U.S. urged to drop policy of confrontation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 23 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary assails the united states for contemplating about the creation of four "rapid strike combat brigades" under the pretext of possible disputes in the Korean peninsula and other Asia-Pacific areas, while frantically staging war drills against the DPRK.
 This is an indication that the U.S. is making the provocation of the second Korean war a fait accompli, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. singled out the "settlement of regional disputes" as a main thrust of its military strategy in view of the new international situation after the demise of the cold war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present U.S. administration is set to escalate the showdown of strength after choosing the Korean peninsula and other Asia-Pacific areas as a major theatre for carrying out the strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean peninsula is made its main target. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have already deployed huge forces in and around South Korea.   Not content with this, they are going to bring a new carrier flotilla and airborne and maritime landing forces there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years they created mobile strike units by reorganizing the U.S. air force stationed in the Asia-Pacific region into 10 expeditionary forces in pursuance of their strategy for a showdown of strength on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. staged such war exercises as a joint mine warfare exercise with the South Korean military authorities in a bid to round off the operational plan to rapidly hurl reinforcements into South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It leaves no doubt that the U.S. bellicose forces would unleash a war of aggression against the DPRK as they designated it as their "no. 1 enemy." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is busy with preparations for a war against the DPRK, while talking about "dialogue." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is well advised to face up to the reality and abandon its reckless policy of confrontation.

Rodong Sinmun calls on all Koreans to display patriotism 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 23 (KCNA) -- National reunification is a patriotic cause achievable only through a patriotic struggle of the whole nation, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 The patriotic spirit of the Korean nation serves as a solid ideological and moral foundation for the great national unity and a driving force for national reunification, The article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There exist a number of differences between the north and the south beside the differing ideology and system. But the primary task before the Korean nation is to achieve national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Patriotism serves as a great banner grouping the Koreans from all walks of life in the north, south and abroad for national unity and reunification, regardless of differences in ideology, system, political view, religious belief, interests of individual class and social strata. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il's policy is the most patriotic all-embracing policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has wisely led the struggle for great national unity and reunification holding aloft the banner of patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Workers' Party of Korea and the DPRK government have exerted all efforts to achieve the cause of national reunification in conformity with the historic circumstances where the inter-Korean relations and the movement for national reunification have entered a new phase unprecedented in its history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation is carrying on its vigorous struggle to frustrate by the concerted efforts of the nation the challenge of the outside and anti-reunification forces and their moves to check the advance of the movement for independent national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans will more vigorously accelerate their march for independent reunification, true to Kim Jong Il's noble patriotic intention.
